    .recipe-container
      h1.recipe-title Chicken Biryani Recipe
      p.recipe-text A flavorful Indian dish made with marinated chicken and fragrant spices.

      h2.ingredients-title Ingredients
      ul.ingredient-list
        li 2 cups basmati rice, soaked
        li 500g chicken, cut into pieces
        li 2 onions, thinly sliced
        li 2 tomatoes, chopped
        li 1/2 cup yogurt
        li 2 tbsp ginger-garlic paste
        li 1/4 cup mint leaves, chopped
        li 1/4 cup cilantro leaves, chopped
        li 1/2 tsp turmeric powder
        li 1 tsp red chili powder
        li 1 tsp garam masala
        li Whole spices (cinnamon, cardamom, cloves)
        li Ghee and oil
        li Salt to taste

      h2.procedure-title Procedure
      p.procedure-step Marinate the chicken with yogurt, ginger-garlic paste, red chili powder, turmeric powder, and salt. Let it sit for at least 1 hour.
      p.procedure-step In a large pot, heat ghee and oil. Add the whole spices and sauté until fragrant.
      p.procedure-step Add sliced onions and sauté until golden brown.
      p.procedure-step Add tomatoes and cook until they turn soft.
      p.procedure-step Add marinated chicken and cook until it's no longer pink.
      p.procedure-step In a separate pot, parboil the soaked rice until 70% cooked. Drain.
      p.procedure-step Layer the chicken and rice in the pot. Sprinkle garam masala, mint, and cilantro leaves.
      p.procedure-step Cover the pot tightly and cook on low heat until the rice is fully cooked and aromatic.
      p.procedure-step Serve the delicious Chicken Biryani with raita and enjoy!

    

